Issue: Copypaste from Host OS to VM in virtualbox not working
Solution (steps):
1. Enable bidirectional data in General->Advanced setting of VM
2. Install VBoxClient (requirement for next step): sudo apt install virtualbox-guest-x11
3. Restart the VBox clipboard module: pkill 'VBoxClient --clipboard' -f & sleep 1 && VBoxClient --clipboard

Issue: mininet-vm (mininet-2.3.0-210211-ubuntu-18.04.5-server-amd64) GUI install
Solution:
1. sudo apt-get update
2. sudo apt-get install xinit x11-xserver-utils mate-desktop-environment-core (minmal mate-desktop)
3. sudo apt-get install virtualbox-guest-x11 (if running on virtualbox)

Issue: How to enable Ctrl+Shift+C and Ctrl+Shift+V:

You’ll need to modify the ~/.Xresources file (or create it if it doesn’t exist) to specify these shortcuts.
1. Edit .Xresources (or create the file if it doesn't exist):
  Open or create the ~/.Xresources file:
   nano ~/.Xresources
2. Add the following lines to enable Ctrl+Shift+C and Ctrl+Shift+V:
  XTerm.vt100.translations: #override \
    Ctrl Shift <Key>C: copy-selection(CLIPBOARD) \n\
    Ctrl Shift <Key>V: insert-selection(CLIPBOARD)
3. Apply the changes by reloading the .Xresources file:
   xrdb -merge ~/.Xresources
4. Restart xterm (or the Mininet xterm windows) to see the changes.


